& [SLMCoreDataContracts] is the data identity contract for SLM v0
  + [contract_uuid] is 9f4789ad-bf65-4ff6-97b0-326a615ef732
  + [slice_id] is SLM-02
  + [depends_on] is SLM_Authority_Source_Rails
  + [status] is accepted_for_downstream_contracts

  & [EpistemicTypeSeparation] is the non-negotiable data boundary
    + [Token] is observation
    + [GrammarCandidate] is evidence
    + [LLMSuggestion] is evidence
    + [CandidateMeaning] is pre-stabilization semantic hypothesis
    + [CandidateRelation] is pre-stabilization relation hypothesis
    + [SupportRecord] is weighted support evidence
    + [ContradictionRecord] is weighted opposition evidence
    + [Glyph] is stabilized semantic identity
    + [SemanticRelation] is stabilized relation between Glyph identities
    + [UncertaintyGlyph] is bounded uncertainty identity
    + [LineageRecord] is provenance bridge from graph object to evidence
    - never: treat Token, GrammarCandidate, LLMSuggestion, CandidateMeaning, or CandidateRelation as Glyph

  & [TokenContract] is the observation unit
    + [natural_key] is input_id plus token_index
    + [required_field] is input_id
    + [required_field] is token_index
    + [required_field] is surface_text
    + [required_field] is normalized_text
    + [optional_field] is source_span
    + [optional_field] is token_shape
    + [lifecycle] is immutable_after_observation

  & [GrammarCandidateContract] is role evidence for a Token
    + [natural_key] is token_id plus grammar_role plus provider_or_rule_id
    + [grammar_role] is noun, verb, adjective, adverb, determiner, preposition, conjunction, auxiliary, modal, punctuation, unknown, or extension
    + [support_weight] is evidence support, not truth
    + [evidence_source] is heuristic, lower_llm, dictionary, morphology, position, structural_rule, or user_rule
    + [status] is active, deferred, contradicted, rejected, or superseded

  & [CandidateMeaningContract] is pre-stabilization semantic hypothesis
    + [natural_key] is evidence_workspace_id plus candidate_meaning_id
    + [meaning_kind] is subject, action, relation, modifier, constraint, reference, or uncertainty_candidate
    + [support_record_set] is SupportRecord references
    + [contradiction_record_set] is ContradictionRecord references
    + [lineage] is required
    - never: enter SemanticGraph before stabilization

  & [GlyphContract] is stabilized semantic identity
    + [surrogate_key] is semantic_id
    + [kind] is subject, action, relation_subject, modifier, constraint, uncertainty, wobble, primer_field, or semantic_trace
    + [label] is descriptive, not identity authority
    + [lineage] is required
    + [stabilization_decision] is required
    + [lifecycle_state] is active, retired, superseded, or preserved_trace
    = must: be append-only after creation except lifecycle events represented separately
    - never: mutate semantic_id

  & [UncertaintyGlyphContract] is bounded unresolved meaning
    + [surrogate_key] is semantic_id
    + [uncertainty_type] is unresolved_role, unresolved_relation, unresolved_subject_boundary, unresolved_reference, contradiction_cluster, low_support_candidate, provider_disagreement, or unresolved_scope
    + [boundary_statement] is required
    + [lineage] is required
    + [candidate_set] is the bounded unresolved alternatives
    = must: be created only when uncertainty is specific enough to preserve
    - never: create one uncertainty glyph per every fleeting hypothesis

  ! [Slice02Complete] is accepted
    @ [support] core identities distinguish observations, evidence, hypotheses, stabilized meaning, uncertainty, and lineage

